text: Kūris is the masculine form of a Lithuanian family name. Its feminine forms are: Kūrienė (married woman or widow) and Kūrytė (unmarried woman). The surname may refer to: *Egidijus Kūris (born 1961), former President of the Constitutional Court of the Republic of Lithuania *Pranas Kūris (born 1938), Lithuanian Judge of the European Court of Justice ==See also== *Kuris (disambiguation) Category:Lithuanian-language surnames
title: Kūris
